    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-07T23:36:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-07T23:36:00-05:00" n="898"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d898">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13122.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Fuller</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-07T22:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 7, 1914, 10 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Joint programme has been signed by Villa and Obregon for establishment of civil
                    form of government. Provides for cessation of present revolutionary and military
                    rule; the appointment of Carranza as Provisional President; the appointment of
                    judges; provision for elections.</p>
                <p>United support of northern and northeastern divisions gives good prospect of
                    acceptance either willing or enforced. This union of forces increases chances of
                    Zapata’s submission.</p>
                <pb facs="0711" n="595" xml:id="pg_595"/>
                <p>Call for convention already issued is unsatisfactory as it includes governors who
                    are Carranza appointees, contrary to plan of Torreon. New programme should be
                    carried out and will so tell Carranza at interview tomorrow noon.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fuller</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
